          <div class="bylaw-card highlight-card">
            <h3>No STR-Specific Regulations</h3>
            <p>Burlington is one of the few GTA cities without dedicated short-term rental bylaws. This means <strong>no license fees</strong>, <strong>no principal residence requirement</strong>, and <strong>no night limits</strong>. However, general property standards and zoning regulations still apply, and the city may introduce STR rules in the future.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bylaw-card">
            <h3>No Principal Residence Rule</h3>
            <p>Unlike <a href="/downtown-toronto-airbnb-management">Toronto</a>, Mississauga, and Oakville, Burlington does not require STRs to be your principal residence. Investment properties can be used for short-term rentals.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bylaw-card">
            <h3>No Night Limit</h3>
            <p>There is no annual cap on the number of nights you can rent your property. Host year-round without restrictions on entire home rentals.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bylaw-card">
            <h3>No Municipal Accommodation Tax</h3>
            <p>Burlington does not charge a MAT. Keep more of your rental income compared to neighboring Oakville (4%) or nearby Toronto (8.5%).</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bylaw-card">
            <h3>Zoning Compliance</h3>
            <p>Your property must comply with Burlington's zoning bylaws. Most residential zones permit short-term rentals, but verify your specific zoning if uncertain.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bylaw-card">
            <h3>Condo Rules May Apply</h3>
            <p>If your property is in a condominium, check your condo corporation's declaration and rules. Some condos restrict or prohibit short-term rentals regardless of city regulations.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bylaw-card">
            <h3>Property Standards</h3>
            <p>All properties must meet Burlington's property standards bylaws for maintenance, safety, and livability. Fire safety equipment and proper maintenance are required.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bylaw-card">
            <h3>Insurance Recommended</h3>
            <p>We strongly recommend $2,000,000+ in liability insurance that explicitly covers short-term rental activity to protect your investment and guests.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bylaws-cta">
          <p>Regulations can change. We monitor Burlington's regulatory landscape and will keep you informed of any developments. <a href="/contact">Contact us</a> to get started.</p>
